harsh this: Individuals discover faith, not organizations that can conceal faith thorough conformity.

Havel called it “hanging a sign”.  An illusion of the thing we hang in the window so that others see and understand. Seen with all the other windows hanging the same sign the illusion is complete. So complete that it’s barely noticed. And that’s the point.

Illusion is what we must push through. Know illusion, know truth. No illusion, no truth. That’s the tension of faith. It is why Moses couldn’t see the face of God. It is why Christ came, to show us a face. A human face.

